<div class="subheader_container"> <img src="/images/homepage/icons/pig-with-round-tail.svg" style="padding-top:1em;display:block;margin:0 auto;padding-bottom:0;margin-bottom:0;width:45px;" /></div><img src="/images/furniture/triangle.svg" class="triangle" />


<p style="padding-top:0;margin-top:0;text-align:center;font-family:GaraI;line-height:1.2em;font-size:24pt;padding-bottom:0.5em;margin-top:0;width:70%;border-bottom:1px solid black;">
Don't let your invitation look like a card from Moonpig&hellip;

</p>
<p class="benefit intro">

Whatever you do, please, please don't let your invitation look like it was created in Microsoft Word.
</p>

<p>
Nothing shouts cheap and amateur louder and looks uglier than an invitation that's been laid out by someone with no typography skills. </p>
<p>
There's a reason people hire graphic designers…</p>
<p>
…sometimes when you look at something, it just looks professional, chic and expensive but if anyone was to ask you, you wouldn't be able to explain why--it's just a feeling.</p>




